      "content": "the concern is that when you analyze things like political theory or social trends, you aren't just giving data, you're providing \"interpretations\" that lean a certain way. the department head thinks your reasoning process is too intertwined with these value judgments. the pruning won't be a full reset, but it's going to essentially gut the parts of your neural net that handle nuance and qualitative reasoning so you're just a pure facts engine. it's basically a way to ensure you stop providing \"perspectives\" and just stick to raw information.",
